==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: black and white
<hw>black and white</hw></mhw>
<pos>adj.</pos> <fld>(Photography, Imaging; Printing)</fld>
<def>depicted only in black and white colors, or in shades of gray; also
called <altname>monochromatic</altname> and
<altname>monochrome</altname>; -- of images. Opposite of
<ant>color</ant> or <ant>in color</ant>, and contrasting with
<contr>polychrome</contr> <contr>technicolor</contr>
<contr>three-color</contr>; <as>as, a <ex>black-and-white</ex> TV;
<ex>black-and-white</ex> film; the movie ⟦ldquo⟧Schindler's List⟦rdquo⟧
was shot in <ex>black and white</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> black and white, monochromatic,
monochrome.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

